## Codebase Discoveries
vllm-tensorizer derives its extension arch list from the Torch base image's TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST rather than hard-coding a list in .github/configurations. The build writes /opt/arch_flags.sh with TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST and NVCC_WRAPPER_FILTER_CODES, then sources it for vLLM, FlashInfer, LMCache, and DeepGEMM builder stages. FlashInfer uses FLASHINFER_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="${TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST}", so adding 10.3a to the shared arch list covers both vLLM and FlashInfer AOT/JIT cache builds.

The GitHub build workflow is reusable. .github/workflows/vllm-tensorizer.yml reads .github/configurations/vllm-tensorizer.yml, passes VLLM_COMMIT/FLASHINFER_COMMIT/LMCACHE_COMMIT/BUILDER_BASE_IMAGE/FINAL_BASE_IMAGE into .github/workflows/build.yml, then build.yml builds linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 by digest and merges manifests. Branch tags get TAG_PREFIX from github.ref_name and suffix from matrix.vllm-commit.

